com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.base.main

Class Std

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gl.vn.me.ko.pies.base.main.Std

  • public final class Std
extends Object
    Provides methods for printing to System.out and System.err that append some useful information to printed strings.

    In case of using Std.outPrintln(...) and Std.errPrintln(...) methods a PREFIX is prepended that contains information on the stream and date. Format of the PREFIX is "[STREAM] [DATE] [THREAD_NAME] - ", where

    • STREAM is Std.StreamType.STDOUT.toString() for System.out and Std.StreamType.STDERR .toString() for System.err
    • DATE represents date formatted with DateTimeFormatter constructed with pattern "yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss.SSSZ" and Constant.LOCALE
    • THREAD_NAME represents name of the Thread that prints to standard stream

    This class also substitutes System.out and System.err streams during initialization, which is initiated from the Main class initialization. Streams are substituted with streams that use a special Charset specific to the Application (specified by the -Dpies.consoleCharset Java option, don't confuse it with Constant.CHARSET).

    One SHOULD use Std to print to standard streams and SHOULD NOT use System.out and System.err directly.
